title: For Sale:  WTS: Pre-ban Colt / Univ Simmonds AR15 20 round mags / clips
postcontent:
Yes I know they are magazines ( not clips ) 

I have for sale: true preban factory Colt AR-15 mags and Univ / Simmonds Ind mags with absolutely no dates or restriction ( LEO / military etc ) stamped on them.

20 round mags are more rare than 30 rounders and are much better at the range / shooting from a bench etc etc. These will function just fine in any Rock River Arms - BushMaster - Colt - Olympic Arms - DPMS etc etc ...

They are in good- used condition ( see pics below ) no dents and the feed lips are all fine, just finish wear on the outside of the mag body itself ( common with these ). I function tested 20-30 random mags in a Colt M4 LE6920 and all performed flawless. Most are Colt mfg mags, some are Adventure Line / or other manuf. All are true mil-spec USGI preban magazines.

I have approx 20 Colt mags left and approx 50 Simmonds / Universal mags left ( same exact pre-ban mag as the Colt's and made on the same exact tooling ) All orders from today forward will be a 4-1 ratio on the mags. Orders of 5 which seem to be the most popular with everyone will be 4 Simmonds / Universal mags and 1 Colt mag. As stated - they are the exact same mag and look identical in everyway ( except the base plate stamp says Simmonds - Universal vs Colt ). If you are wanting 10 or 20 mags .... the same 4 to 1 ratio applies: 8 Simmonds / 2 Colts ( order of 10 ) or 16 Simmonds / 4 Colts ( order of 20 ). The Simmonds mags are actually more rare than the Colts and are actually worth more and far more desirable to collectors. The price stays the same at $20ea mag.


Yes I am from WA state and yes I am familiar w/ firearm laws and know that NY - MA / other New England area residents have to use preban mags manuf'd prior to '94 I believe ( basically pre- assault weapons ban era )

My price is $20ea.

I will check to see how many fits in a USPS flat rate Priority mail box ( I am guessing around 25 or so ). Possible $ discount for buying more than 20 mags.

Buyer ( you ) covers the shipping costs and payment is via USPS money order only. No PayPal and no personal checks.

I found these mags locally via an estate sale and figured I would offer them for sale here.

E-mail me at REDACTED and please include a contact phone number in your reply.

edited to add: All buyers need to be in compliance with your district / state laws regarding high-capacity mags. 

pics:

http://i240.photobucket.com/albums/ff295/strkaliten/coltMag20close.jpg?t=REDACTED

http://i240.photobucket.com/albums/ff295/strkaliten/coltMag20far.jpg?t=REDACTED

Army and late Air Force contract mags made by Simmonds. Dull alloy followers and gold/bronze colored anodizing. (Simmonds was a division of Okay/Universal Industries). Made from 1966-1971. Floorplates stamped:

(S Logo) M16/M16A1 CAL 5.56 mm
UNIVERSAL INDS. DIV

Unfortunately, I had to sell my pistol earlier this year and am hoping to find a good home for these brand new parts. Here is a spare parts thread from xdtalk.com that may be helpful: http://www.xdtalk.com/forums/general-sa-xd-xd-m-talk/94824-xd-spare-parts.html.

I purchased everything for $130.09, will sell everyting together for $100 (about 25% off) FTF.  I will also ship for cost.  Thanks for looking!
